"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">v.</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">σός</ref> </xr> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0013.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:3\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.3</biblScope></bibl>.—The separated forms, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σοῦ αὐτοῦ, αὐτοῦ σοῦ</foreign>, etc., were used in <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Att.\">Att.</a></gram></gramGrp>, not as reflexive, but as emphat. personal pronouns, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0059.tlg023:472b\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Grg.\">Grg.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">472b</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0085.tlg004.perseus-grc1:632\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.\">A.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Th.\">Th.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">632</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}